HEADWORD: Jurisconsult
<hw>Ju`ris*con"sult</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>jurisconsultus</ets>; <ets>jus</ets>, <ets>juris</ets>, right +
<ets>consulere</ets>, <ets>consultum</ets>, to consult: cf. F.
<ets>jurisconsulte</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A man learned in
the civil law; an expert in juridical science; a professor of
jurisprudence; a jurist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

